---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHero from '../../components/SectionHero.astro';
import ContentCTA from '../../components/ContentCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Best Password Managers for Small Business 2026"
  description="Compare Bitwarden, 1Password, Dashlane, NordPass & Keeper. Pricing, features, security, and which one is right for your team."
>
  <SectionHero
    icon="🔑"
    title="Password Manager Comparison"
    description="Stop reusing passwords. Stop storing them in spreadsheets. We tested the top 5 password managers for small business — here is which one you should pick based on your team size, budget, and technical comfort level."
    badge="⭐ Honest Review · FTC Affiliate Disclosure"
    gradient="from-primary-950 via-primary-900 to-primary-800"
  />

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 p-4 text-sm text-yellow-800 mb-10">
        <strong>⚖️ Affiliate Disclosure:</strong> Some links below are affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you purchase, at no extra cost to you. Ratings are based on our testing, not commission rates.
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Why Your Business Needs a Password Manager</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        The #1 cause of data breaches is still reused and weak passwords. Your team is reusing passwords across services — guaranteed. When (not if) one of those services gets breached, attackers try those same credentials on your email, your bank, your cloud storage. A password manager eliminates password reuse, generates strong unique passwords, and makes secure sharing possible without sticky notes or spreadsheets.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10">What We Tested</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Product</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Business Plan</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Free Tier</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">MFA Built-in</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold">Best For</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Bitwarden</td><td class="text-center">$6/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-accent-700 font-semibold">✅ Yes</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Budget-conscious teams</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">1Password</td><td class="text-center">$7.99/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-gray-400">❌ No</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Best overall UX & family plans</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Dashlane</td><td class="text-center">$8/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-gray-400">Limited</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Dark web monitoring included</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">NordPass</td><td class="text-center">$3.99/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-gray-400">Limited</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Nord ecosystem users</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Keeper</td><td class="text-center">$3.75/user/month</td><td class="text-center text-gray-400">❌ No</td><td class="text-center">✅</td><td class="text-center">Compliance-heavy industries</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <ContentCTA
        icon="🔐"
        title="Test Your Password Strength First"
        description="Before picking a manager, see how strong your current passwords are. Our free checker analyzes entropy and crack time."
        href="/tools/password-checker/"
        ctaText="Check Password Strength →"
      />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10">Detailed Reviews</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">1. Bitwarden — Best Value for Small Teams</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Bitwarden is open-source, independently audited, and offers the most generous free tier of any password manager. The free plan already covers unlimited passwords across unlimited devices — enough for a solo business. The Teams plan at $6/user/month adds shared collections, admin console, user management, and priority support. For most small businesses with 2-50 employees, Bitwarden is the best balance of price and capability. The interface is functional but less polished than 1Password or Dashlane — if your team values aesthetics, look elsewhere. If you value security and price, Bitwarden is the clear winner.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">2. 1Password — Best User Experience</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        1Password has the most polished interface, excellent sharing via vaults, and a unique "Secret Key" that adds an extra layer of encryption beyond your master password. The Business plan at $7.99/user/month includes unlimited shared vaults, admin controls, and free family accounts for every team member — a nice perk. Watchtower alerts you to compromised websites and weak passwords. Best for teams where UX matters and the budget is not the primary constraint.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">3. Dashlane — Best for Dark Web Monitoring</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Dashlane's standout feature is built-in dark web monitoring that scans for your company credentials on breach databases and dark web markets. It also includes a VPN (though a password manager VPN is not a substitute for a real VPN). The Business plan at $8/user/month is the priciest option, but the credential monitoring alone may justify the cost for businesses handling sensitive client data. The free tier is limited to 25 passwords — essentially a trial.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">4. NordPass — Best Budget Pro Plan</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        From the makers of NordVPN, NordPass offers competitive pricing at $3.99/user/month for business. It lacks the polish of 1Password and the open-source transparency of Bitwarden, but provides solid core functionality: password generation, autofill, secure sharing, and a data breach scanner. If you already use NordVPN for your team, the bundle pricing makes NordPass attractive.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">5. Keeper — Best for Regulated Industries</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Keeper positions itself for business and enterprise with compliance certifications including SOC 2, ISO 27001, and FedRAMP. It offers detailed activity reporting, role-based access control, and advanced provisioning via SCIM and Azure AD integration. For law firms, medical practices, and financial services that need compliance-grade password management with audit trails, Keeper is the strongest choice. The Business plan starts at $3.75/user/month but key compliance features require the Enterprise tier.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10">Our Recommendation</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>🟢 Solo business or tight budget:</strong> Bitwarden Free → Teams ($6/user/month as you grow)</li>
          <li><strong>🟢 Best overall for small teams (2-50):</strong> Bitwarden Teams or 1Password Business</li>
          <li><strong>🟡 Need dark web monitoring:</strong> Dashlane Business</li>
          <li><strong>🟡 Already using NordVPN:</strong> NordPass for bundle savings</li>
          <li><strong>🔴 Compliance-heavy (HIPAA, SOC 2):</strong> Keeper Enterprise</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
